    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-04-07T15:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-04-07T15:41:00-05:00" n="204"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">504.418A2/247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Diekema</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-07T21:00:00+00:19"
                            >April 7, 1930—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 7—8:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. Conference number 21. From Miller. At commission on territorial waters April
                    7, I proposed that the commission abandon all idea of a signed convention and
                    submit to the Governments for their future consideration and study a report of
                    the studies and deliberations of the commission; that action will be followed.
                    There will be no convention or draft convention on territorial waters but merely
                    a report of the commission which will contain an account of the proceedings, the
                    points of agreement and of difference and drafts of certain articles
                    provisionally agreed upon and hoping for a further conference on the subject in
                    the future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Diekema</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
